---
description: Require `server-only` in server actions, repositories, and other server-only modules so they cannot be bundled into client code by mistake
globs: src/actions/**/*.{ts,tsx},src/**/actions/**/*.{ts,tsx},src/**/*actions*.{ts,tsx},src/**/repositories/**/*.ts,src/lib/prisma.ts,src/app/api/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

Server-only guard (server-only)

Use the official Next.js pattern so server-only code is never pulled into the client graph by accident. The server-only package throws at build time if a Client Component or client hook imports the module.

Any file that is meant to run only on the server (and any shared module that must never be imported from client code) must start with import "server-only" as described below.

Where server actions live (see react-features-architecture): cross-feature / general-purpose → src/actions/<area>/; feature-specific (e.g. Prisma for one domain) → src/features/<feature>/actions/. Both need import "server-only" when the implementation is server-only.

When to add it

Add import "server-only" as the first import (after any file-level comments) in:

Server Actions — any file that uses "use server" (whole file or exported functions), including under src/actions/ and src/features/<feature>/actions/, and files named like *-actions.ts.
Repositories / DB — modules under src/features//repositories/ and src/lib/prisma.ts (or other server-only data clients).
App Router API route handlers — files under src/app/api/ (e.g. route.ts).
Other server-only libraries — any src/lib/ module (or feature module) that uses secrets, DB, filesystem, or other Node/server-only APIs and must not be imported from "use client" trees.

Pattern

import "server-only"

import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma"
// …rest of imports

Do not import server-only from client components or from modules imported by "use client" files.
If a server action file only re-exports from a repository that already has import "server-only", the action file should still include its own import "server-only" at the top so the action module is explicitly marked—imports of the action from client code fail at the action boundary.

Dependency

The server-only package must be listed in package.json dependencies (bun add server-only).
